string.replace() 
<br></br>
a <em>method</em> that returns a <em>new</em> string with some or all matched of a pattern replaced by a replacement.
<br></br>
ex: let str = 'hello there'
<br></br>
let newStr = str.replace('there', 'friend');
console.log(newStr) ==> 'hello friend'
<br></br>
if there are multiple values that are the same - ex. "hello there there" - it would only replace the first one and not the second
<br></br>
you could instead use .replaceAll() 
